---
import { Layout } from '@/layouts';

/** One readable measure; title + body share it so edges line up. */
const measure = 'w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto';
const body = 'text-lg text-muted-foreground text-comic leading-relaxed';
const h2 = 'text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-fun';
const miniThumb =
  'shrink-0 w-36 h-36 sm:w-40 sm:h-40 rounded-xl border border-dashed border-muted-foreground/25 shadow-sm';
/** Wide block for a future team / company group photo */
const groupPhotoPlaceholder =
  'w-full aspect-[21/9] rounded-xl border border-dashed border-muted-foreground/25 shadow-sm bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-200/85 via-muted/80 to-primary/15 dark:from-slate-800/55 dark:via-muted/40 dark:to-primary/25';
---

<Layout
  title="About Us - 4M Industrial Development Limited"
  description="We believe toys should spark a chain reaction in creativity and confidence. Since 1993, 4M has designed STEM kits in Hong Kong that turn curiosity into lifelong learning."
>
  <div class="container-custom py-8 md:py-12 lg:py-14">
    <main class={`${measure} space-y-14 md:space-y-16 lg:space-y-20`} aria-label="About 4M">
      <!-- Hero title -->
      <header>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-[2.65rem] font-bold text-fun leading-tight text-balance text-foreground">
          We believe toys should spark a chain reaction in{' '}
          <span class="font-fredoka font-semibold text-primary dark:text-sky-400">creativity</span>
          {' '}and{' '}
          <span class="font-fredoka font-semibold text-secondary dark:text-amber-300">confidence</span>
        </h1>
      </header>

      <div
        class={groupPhotoPlaceholder}
        role="img"
        aria-label="Placeholder for company or team group photo"
      />

      <!-- Opening -->
      <div class="space-y-6" aria-labelledby="about-opening-heading">
        <h2 id="about-opening-heading" class="sr-only">Why 4M</h2>
        <p class={body}>
          At 4M, we believe a toy shouldn't just be something a child plays with—it should be the start of a chain
          reaction.
        </p>
        <p class={body}>
          It starts with a box, but it ends with a discovery that changes how a child sees the world. Our mission is to
          provide the "spark" that turns curiosity into a lifelong passion for learning, creating, and questioning.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Everyday ideas -->
      <section class="space-y-10 md:space-y-12" aria-labelledby="about-everyday-heading">
        <header class="space-y-4">
          <h2 id="about-everyday-heading" class={h2}>
            From Everyday Object to Extraordinary Ideas
          </h2>
          <p class={body}>
            We don't just sell kit, we sell an 'aha' moment. We take the mundane and make it magnetic.
          </p>
        </header>

        <ul class="list-none space-y-12 md:space-y-14 p-0 m-0" role="list">
          <li
            class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-8 sm:items-center"
            data-about-mini="potato"
          >
            <div
              class={`${miniThumb} bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-200/90 to-yellow-600/30 dark:from-amber-900/45 dark:to-yellow-900/40 mx-auto sm:mx-0 sm:shrink-0`}
              role="img"
              aria-label="Product image placeholder: potato clock or similar kit"
            />
            <div class="min-w-0 flex-1 space-y-2 text-left">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground text-comic">The Power of a Potato</h3>
              <p class={body}>
                It's not just a vegetable; it's the battery that brings a digital clock to life.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li
            class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row-reverse gap-6 sm:gap-8 sm:items-center"
            data-about-mini="dig"
          >
            <div
              class={`${miniThumb} bg-gradient-to-br from-stone-200/90 to-amber-800/25 dark:from-stone-700/50 dark:to-amber-950/40 mx-auto sm:mx-0 sm:shrink-0`}
              role="img"
              aria-label="Product image placeholder: dig / excavation kit"
            />
            <div class="min-w-0 flex-1 space-y-2 text-left">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground text-comic">The Thrill of the Dig</h3>
              <p class={body}>
                It's not just a block of plaster; it's a prehistoric mystery waiting for a young paleontologist to
                unearth a T-Rex.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li
            class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-6 sm:gap-8 sm:items-center"
            data-about-mini="upcycling"
          >
            <div
              class={`${miniThumb} bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-200/90 to-emerald-700/25 dark:from-slate-700/45 dark:to-emerald-950/45 mx-auto sm:mx-0 sm:shrink-0`}
              role="img"
              aria-label="Product image placeholder: upcycling / can robot kit"
            />
            <div class="min-w-0 flex-1 space-y-2 text-left">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-foreground text-comic">The Future of Upcycling</h3>
              <p class={body}>
                A discarded soda can isn't trash—it's the chassis for a solar-powered rover or a walking robot.
              </p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Philosophy -->
      <section class="space-y-6 pb-4" aria-labelledby="about-philosophy-heading">
        <h2 id="about-philosophy-heading" class={h2}>
          The 4M Philosophy
        </h2>
        <p class={body}>
          Since 1993, our Hong Kong-based design team has been obsessed with the Four Minds: being Imaginative,
          Creative, Inspiring, and Fun. We know that when a child builds a robot with their own hands, they aren't just
          practicing eye-hand coordination—they are building the confidence to realize they can solve problems, invent
          solutions, and shape the future.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>
